definition: to hit (the mark)/to be hit by/to suffer/to win (a prize, a lottery)

sentences.english: If you have insurance under a student plan, it probably will end in mid-August.
sentences.chinese: 如果你买的是学生险，保险可能会在八月中旬到期。

sentences.english: It was now the middle of June, and the weather fine;
sentences.chinese: 眼下正是六月中旬，天清气朗。

sentences.english: In mid-month, Ken Starr announced he was stepping down.
sentences.chinese: 中旬，斯塔尔宣布即将离任。

sentences.chinese: 曼联7月中旬就要自2004年以来第一次西行。

sentences.chinese: 这个湖通常到了一月中旬就封冻了。

sentences.chinese: 经典帆布鞋面为补充的风格上诉中旬剪影。

sentences.english: The studio is still under construction and won't open until mid-March.
sentences.chinese: 这个工作室仍在筹建中，明年三月中旬才能营业。

sentences.chinese: 我们的草坪要到五月中旬才变绿。

sentences.english: The period with moderate climate and relatively less desert wind is from the middle of April to the middle of October.
